        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=6235&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Questions+about+PvP+classes+on+SZ"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">As a necro on a blue server, my PvP skills and knowledge are a bit lacking.  I was thinking about starting a new char on the SZ server, but am a bit confused on which class to play.</P><P>I'm looking for a class that can PvP well, can defend against a surprise PvP attack well, and also has a bit to offer groups in the PvE game.</P><P>A few of the abilities that I think would be important on a PvP server:<BR>1) Invis<BR>2) See Invis<BR>3) Bind and Gate<BR>4) Root / snare<BR>5) Some kind of attack (melee or DD)<BR>6) A pet of some kind<BR>7) SoW<BR>8) Teleports</P><P>With that in mind, I thought a mage would be a good class.  However, when the pet dies (or is rooted or just ignored) then things turn sour fast.</P><P>Shamans seem like a good choice, and I hear they can solo well.  They also bring a lot to the PvE game later in life.  Druids also seem like a good class, with a lot of the benefits of shamans plus the addition of snare and teleports (though no pet and no slow or quickness).</P><P>I'm pretty sure I want to create a good character, as it would be more of a challange.  The evils on Kunark might as well be playing on a blue server, I can't imagaine that many goods will be hunting there for a while.</P><P>Also, the way I understand the point system, looting rights, and insignias is that you need to make the killing blow to loot the corpse.  So some classes (clerics and enchanters) might not be the best choice under these rules.</P><P>At the moment I imagine that peoples resists are close to where they started.  Being a new server, with little plat and loot around.  However, as the server matures, resists will play more of a role in being able to land spells on other folks.  So maybe a mage would be good for a while, then as I level and the evils are leveling their resists will get higher thereby rendering my DDs less effective.</P><P>Anyway, I'd be interested in hearing from the PvPers around here about their thoughts.</P><P>I think this format would be helpful to me:<BR>Class...........level..................PvP............................PvE<BR>Shaman.......1-33........strengths/weaknesses.......strengths/weaknesses<BR>Shaman......34-50.......strengths/weaknesses.......strengths/weaknesses<BR>Shaman......51-60.......strengths/weaknesses.......strengths/weaknesses</P><P>Thanks in advance for the help.</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>

