        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=47880&TOPIC_ID=6235&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Questions+about+PvP+classes+on+SZ&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">The largest factor in deciding what's "good" at PVP or not is player skill. Mages can win many fights if the player knows what they're doing, and wizards can lose a fight if they're stupid.</P><P>That said, there's still certain classes that will always have a rougher time in PVP. Mages are one of them. Pets are incredibly easy to neutralize, and once a mage loses his pet he's dead.</P><P>Shaman are reportedly very good in PVP. Druids and wizards are popular because of their ports.. which is a valuable tool in PVP. Bards are probably THE most popular, because they're so freaking hard to kill. Rangers are also quite powerful, believe it or not. Enchanters are decent, but only against people with low MR. </P><P>Basically, versatility in PVP means you win. The fewer options you have, the worse you'll do.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

