        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Xzzy, thanks for the information.  I'd heard that bards were a good PvP class, but I don't have the patience or desire to twist songs all day long.</P><P>Having never played on a PvP server, I expect to take a few lumps.  That's part of the fun and the learning process.  What I don't want to do though, is choose a class (like a mage) that might be easy to play at first, but will have a harder time later in life.  I'm also leery of playing a class that has such a huge Achilles Heal with their pet.  Enchanters are in a similar boat with most of their spells being MR based (though the 150% effectiveness of debuffs will make Tash that much more useful).</P><P>Druids seem like a natural PvP class; SoW, root, snare, DoTs, DDs, healing and ports.  Lots to offer a group in PvE, and they have great soloing ability as well, but questionable value to a 50+ level group later in life.</P><P>Shaman seem like a great class; SoW, root, DoTs, decent DDs, some healing and regen, great speed buffs and debuffs, and a decent pet.  Cani would also be great to have, and they get some great stat buffs, resist buffs and malise.  They seem to solo well, and have a lot to offer groups.</P><P>Rangers, rogues, paladins, and warriors have their strengths.  But the lack of binding seems to me a real problem on a PvP server.  Traveling sucks in general, and traveling on a PvP server when more than 70% of the players want to kill you sucks even more.  The inability to SoW, bind, and gate seems to be a big headache.  Maybe I'm just making a bigger problem out of it than it is.</P><P>Already talked about mages.  I'm not sure I want to be so mana dependant like wizards are.  I don't want to med, med, med, nuke, med, med, med, nuke all day long.  But wizards do get great DDs, root and port.</P><P>Anyone else have any thoughts?</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
