        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I thouroughly disagree.  PvP is class based, skill has very very little to do with it.  A necro can stand toe to toe with a mage and kill with just chain defluxes and there is NOTHING the mage can do.  Best thing would be to gate :p</P><P>Once you attain mastery of your class, its all timing and spell choice, and that doesnt take a great deal of skill.</P><P>Best class for you would probably be either a wizard, enchanter, or necro.  Wizards are just brainless to pvp with, stand and pound hotkeys.  They have root for low level immobilization and their DD can kill pretty much any other caster, aside from one who really knows how to kill wizards.  Enchanters have by far the most immobilization options (root/mez/blind/whirl/str debuffs etc), but take a long time to really get used to.  Necros have the most staying power, being able to lifetap and gate as well as have a forimdable offense means you shouldnt die much, even before you get Harmshield.</P><P>/shrug.  Ask me about a specific class and level range and Ill let you know what I think :)</P><P>-Jalest<BR>Rallos Zek</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
