        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">druids are a good pvp class, if all else fails they can run away and send charmed pets at their opponent, plus with soc they can get out of casting range very easily</P><P>however I would go with a shaman personlly...  Just becasue when you are not actually engaged with another person you are much more valuable to a group then a druid...  I hate playing a druid in a group, my heals all suck and my buffs are inferior to a shaman, all I can do is snare and crappy nuke(sure it's half the mana and hlaf the casting time of the wizard dd at my level, but its half damage too) anyway a shaman gets a pet at later levels and its not too bad either.  If you can wait this long, maybe you should make a beastmaster when sol comes out, since they seem so solo oriented(thus having lots of options open in a given situation) perhpas they will be good pvpers...</P><P><font color=red>WARNING THE FOLLOWING IS A SIG AND IS IN NO WAY AFFILIATED WITH THE ABOVE POST </font id=red> <font color=yellow> (it is intended to be funny, however is more likely not) </font id=yellow> now there is no room for an actual message here<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
