        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I have a 30 necro on SZ now. One of the things I'm starting to realize is that although I feel very comfortable in a 1-1 situation, 1-1 fights rarely present themselves. Usually a fight is </P><P>* 2-3 PKers attacking an unprepared group<BR>* a highbie running into a lowbie</P><P>Class doesn't really matter in either of these two scenarios. In the first, its the ogranized PKers that will win. In the second, the highbie will win. </P><P>I think Shaman is pretty nice, and I've considered remaking as an iksar shaman (iksar necro now). In fights the most important factor seems to be SoW. On the other hand, harmshield and shadowstep are so good when I run into PvP that I don't know if I can live without them. 1.0 sec casting time rules.</P><P>Morloth X`Mal<BR>Bertoxx Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
