        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">If you are attacked by 2 or 3 players, I guess your only hope is you are SoWed and somehow not rooted or snared, or that you can root them first and take them out of the fight.  In both of these cases a shaman or druid would seem good.</P><P>I am interesteded in playing on the good side, so a necro is out.  I also don't want to be a wizard, never really appealed to me.</P><P>I guess I keep coming back to a druid or shaman.  Seems like a shaman would have a bit more to offer a group, and they can solo well.  I also don't like the idea of being classified with the other d00ds around EQ, so that seems to leave a barbarian shaman.  Shamans also get some decent armor, so they should surrive a straight melee attack better than an INT caster or druid.</P><P>To all the PvPers out there; all things being equal (level, equipment, surprise) are shaman a good class to PvP with?</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
